ind.kdtree

Class KDTree

  • java.lang.Object
    • ind.kdtree.KDTree

  • public class KDTree
extends java.lang.Object
    Implements a k-d-tree and some essential functions. A k-d-tree is defined by a root node and by the descriptor type and dimensionality used. This class provides functions for constructing a k-d-tree, adding an image to a given tree, checking whether a tree contains a specified image, removing an image and a function for performing a nearest neighbor search.
    Author:
    Matej Stanic

      • searchNode

        private static final void searchNode(ImageContainer image,
              KDNode node,
              int num,
              java.util.TreeSet<KDNode> results,
              java.util.Set<KDNode> examined,
              DescriptorType type,
              Metric metric)
        Helper function for the nearest neighbor search. The algorithm checks whether there could be any points on the other side of the splitting plane that are closer to the search point than the current best. In concept, this is done by intersecting the splitting hyperplane with a hypersphere around the search point that has a radius equal to the current nearest distance. Since the hyperplanes are all axis-aligned this is implemented as a simple comparison to see whether the difference between the splitting coordinate of the search point and current node is less than the distance (overall coordinates) from the search point to the current best.
